In a saucepan, heat 1/4 cup oil. Add onions and saute 4 minutes. Add jalapenos and cumin seeds and saute until fragrant. Add the cloves, cinnamon and coriander. When fragrant, add the ginger, mangoes and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cook until mangoes are soft. Add the lime juice, vinegar, 1/4 cup vegetable oil, 1 cup water and sugar. Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until thick. Add salt and pepper. Cool completely. Put in glass jars and store in the refrigerator for up to 2 months.